  "notes": [
    "Born of epic #1967 M2 — single spec authored 2026-06-19 closing the link-8 cascade-feedback loop for the 70 measured BEH-* parameters that had no AGGREGATE/ADAPT consumer (companion 16 + personality-adaptation 12 + supervision 11 + engagement 8 + curriculum-adaptation 7 + learning-adaptation 5 + reinforcement 5 + onboarding 5 + behavior-core 1).",
    "Single-spec / multi-section design chosen over 9-spec-per-domain because most groups are universal (no profileCondition gating); per-trigger fanout achieves the same activation semantics with one source of truth.",
    "Threshold conventions: 5-tier (mastery/secure/developing/emerging/no_evidence) for quality / competency dimensions, 3-tier semantic (high/moderate/low or honoured/partial/drift or rising/stable/declining) for preference / fidelity / trend dimensions. Pedagogy review is free to retune any cut-point — these are reasonable defaults to close the structural loop.",
    "ADAPT-stage adaptation targets (BEH-*-ADAPTATION) are tutor-side; aggregating them as 'fidelity' tracks per-session whether the prescribed target was honoured — orthogonal to the LEARNER signal being measured.",
    "BEH-MOOD / BEH-ENERGY are session-state signals — aggregation tracks the TYPICAL level across the rolling window, not absolute current-call value.",
    "SUPV-001 scores are agent-compliance signals; per-caller roll-up reveals whether the agent's behaviour with THIS caller drifts from the operator-set norms (different from the per-call alarm semantics of the raw SUPV scores)."
  ]
}
